The paper deals with the problem of learning the structure of object categories in computer vision, which is a core topic in the field of computer vision. The paper proposes a novel unsupervised approach that can discover and learn landmarks in object categories, thus characterizing their structure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a deep neural network for detecting landmarks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of regression, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural and man-made objects, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
